<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<h2 id="head-c2f4e69d23b8ac5cc25a88ea5f5c97889fcb080d"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/classic/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/classic/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>The Ring of Flare</h2>
<p>
<em>The mighty ring of the Thunderlord Flare that makes the wearer strong and healthy. It was once a ring of power and has been given to Flare by Celegorm when he arrived on Middle-earth with a full nest of Thunderlords.</em> 
</p>
<p>
It can be activated for <strong>dimension door</strong> every <strong>100</strong> turns if it is being worn. It grants you the power of <strong>swap position</strong> if it is being worn. It increases your <strong>strength</strong>, <strong>constitution</strong>, <strong>charisma</strong> and <strong>searching</strong> by <strong>3</strong>. It provides <strong>immunity</strong> to <strong>fire</strong>. It allows you to <strong>fly</strong>. It allows you to see <strong>invisible</strong> monsters. It allows you to sense the presence of <strong>thunderlords</strong>. It cannot be harmed by <strong>acid</strong>, <strong>cold</strong>, <strong>lightning</strong> or <strong>fire</strong>. 
</p>
<p>
If you've found this, some part of the RNG loves you. This is one of the best rings in the game! Especially for warriors, but all classes benefit.  
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Point one: fire immunity, sought after but rarely acquired.  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Point two: fighter-based stat boosts, as well as charisma and searching, which most fighters lack.  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Point three: flight, allowing you the twin advantages of levitate and tree walking.  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Point four: dimension door, which works even on no-teleport levels such as Mt. Doom. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
This is definitely an excellent ring that you should wear right now, if not sooner. In fact, in a_info it's noted that if its stat boosts were raised it may be more tempting than even *that* ring... 
</p>
<h2 id="head-ff11f0da0a4cd245270f188d8a7299b4084d0328"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/classic/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/classic/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Chatter</h2>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: This ring, while having all of the above wonderful attributes, is not necessarily a must-wear ring for all characters. (And btw, who says fire immunity is rarely acquired?!) Its primary usefulness for some characters is the dimension door attribute, used as a swap-out ring in places such as Mt. Doom. <p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Fire immunity can only be found on 11 non-random artifacts (7 without counting cursed and ultimate items), but luckily there are enough random artifacts with this immunity. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Heh. See the discussion between Neil and myself on my homepage: 
</p>

    <ol type="1">

    <li>
<p>
'trueart' he doesn't like that term 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
